<br>
We just had our water heater go out a bit before Christmas and had to replace that.  We had another surprise after that with the damn cat (Not Virest, no lol) that ate up some more Christmas money.  Then, our heat just went out.  While we were still a merry bunch it looked like our Christmas was shaping up not to have everything we wanted for the kids.  We were calling people to try and find someone here to fix it before we left town and so we would freeze tonight.  The first guy who was around never called us back when we paged him to come do it (we had to check the costs out and make sure the funds available).  Well after calling we finally found somebody.  $95 Sunday rate minimum hour and a half.  Then parts, etc...  Looks like there goes another $250 of the $750 we had set aside for Christmas which would leave us the $150 we already spent on the kids plus maybe another hundred.  Not a great Christmas.  Its been a little harder to live as we used to since I left my investment advisor career to go back and get my masters for a career change.  Well, I let the guy know we had to check how we wanted to pay and could he give us a call back in 5 minutes. He said he would call his supervisor and see if he could bill us.  Well, instead, I get a call back and the guy just says with what he knows, he thinks he can just talk me through the repair.  HOOT! No money going out.  Sure enough, we were lucky to have it fixed 30 minutes later and, luckily, it did not require a part.  The part was able to be cleaned and made functioning again.  How much do you want to bet anyone else who had come to fix it would have charged us the hour-and-a-half and replaced the part?<br>
<br>
That just says someone out there gives a @#%$.  <br>
<br>
Here's to people who give a crap... /cheers<br>
